07486nmm a2200913Ia 9789633865903DE-B159720240328111612.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240328t20232023hu     fo  d z      eng d  a97896338659037 a10.1515/97896338659032doi  a(DE-B1597)633209  a(OCoLC)1356967015  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ahucHU 4aH61.15 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04a300.1223/eng/2023010500aOpen Society Unresolved :bThe Contemporary Relevance of a Contested Idea /ced. by Christof Royer, Liviu Matei. 1aBudapest ;aNew York : bCentral European University Press, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (228 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction: Open Society Unresolved: Charting the Contested Terrain -- tPART I. Philosophical and Theoretical Perspectives on Open Society -- t1 HUMAN NATURE AND THE OPEN SOCIETY -- t2 IN PRAISE OF COLDNESS: THE OPEN NEIGHBORHOOD AND ITS ENEMIES -- t3 AGAINST IDENTITY: INDIVIDUALITY AS THE FOUNDATION OF OPEN SOCIETY -- t4 EMPIRICAL EMBODIMENT OF CRITICAL RATIONALISM: DELIBERATIVE THEORY AND OPEN SOCIETY -- t5 OPEN SOCIETY AS AN ACHIEVEMENT: POPPER, GAUS, AND THE LIBERAL TRADITION -- t6 NOZICK'S META-UTOPIA AS AN OPEN SOCIETY -- t7 HANNAH ARENDT AND LITERARY PEDAGOGY -- t8 CAN BERGSON'S DEFINITION OF OPEN SOCIETY BE USEFUL TODAY? -- tPART II National and Regional Perspectives on Open Society -- t9 THE GENDER OF ILLIBERALISM: NEW TRANSNATIONAL ALLIANCES AGAINST OPEN SOCIETIES IN CENTRAL AND EASTERN EUROPE -- t10 OPEN SOCIETY CONTESTED: LIBERAL UNIVERSALISM VERSUS AUTOCRATIC FUNCTIONALISM IN HONG KONG -- t11 "SOROSOIDS": USES OF LABELING IN BULGARIA -- t12 AN AFRICAN BACKGROUND TO THE CONCEPT OF OPEN SOCIETY: IKENGA AND OFO CULTIC FIGURES AS STRUCTURAL REPRESENTATIONS OF THE ENTERPRISING SPIRIT OF THE IGBO OF NIGERIA -- t13 IMAGINING THE FUTURE OF INTELLIGENCE IN OPEN SOCIETIES: VENTURING BEYOND SECRECY AND SCIENTIFIC PROPHECY AS TOTALITARIAN MODES OF MODERNITY -- t14 OPEN SOCIETY IN CRISIS: MAKING SENSE OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND EXPERT ADVICE DURING COVID-19 -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2fd2star  aIs the concept of open society still relevant in the 21st century? Do the current social, moral, and political realities call for a drastic revision of this concept? Here fifteen essays address real-world contemporary challenges to open society from a variety of perspectives. What unites the individual authors and chapters is an interest in open society's continuing usefulness and relevance to address current problems. And what distinguishes them is a rich variety of geographical and cultural backgrounds, and a wide range of academic disciplines and traditions. While focusing on probing the contemporary relevance of the concept, several chapters approach it historically. The book features a comprehensive introduction to the history and current 'uses' of the theory of open society. The authors link the concept to contemporary themes including education, Artificial Intelligence, cognitive science, African cosmology, colonialism, and feminism. The diversity of viewpoints in the analysis reflects a commitment to plurality that is at the heart of this book and of the idea of open society itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aLiberalism. 0aSocial sciencesxPhilosophy. 0aSocial structure. 0aUniversalism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aOpen society.  acontemporary relevance.  adiversity and plurality.  ageographically and intellectually global.  atheory and practice.1 aBoutayeb, Rachid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aC